//text: Early app concepts were based on the team’s previous experiment with a fully featured web platform, but that approach failed. When I joined the team, we shifted the focus to mobile and aimed to make lesson creation easier.

//gallery: @Identity

//text: After ideating around multiple content types and extensively testing the mobile editor, we made a difficult decision to remove it from the app entirely. It may sound counterintuitive, but after 20+ interviews and a survey of 500+ early users, we found that our first audience was not early-stage authors, but experienced experts working with content creation teams.

//text: To fit their needs, I designed the app around a social media-friendly format. I also created content guidelines so users could create not only video lessons, but also text-based content.

